{"TopicId":157637,"ForumId":70,"TopicTitle":"Spontaneous orbit change.","CreatedByName":"grixt","CreatedById":175798,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-12T14:48:13Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"grixt","CreatedById":175798,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-03-12T14:48:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI run into a troublesome situation. A problem started to appear a few days ago.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EKSP:\u003C/strong\u003E 1.2.2.1622 Win32\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EProblem:\u003C/strong\u003E Eva-ed kerbals,\u00A0decoupled and detached stages/parts spontaneously\u00A0changing orbit via Radial-in always end up on a\u00A0crash course. Also impossible\u00A0to use timewarp focusing eva-ed kerbal\u00A0or detached stage due to phantom acceleration. It prevents me from completing rescue missions or any spacewalk operations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EModlist\u003C/strong\u003E:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://pastebin.com/J70VvHGh\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://pastebin.com/J70VvHGh\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ESteps\u003C/strong\u003E: I can recreate it with these steps.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Build\u00A0a rocket capable of going into\u00A0circular orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. Launch it manually or with MJ2 into any height orbit. Stages detached in process will quickly loose its altitude.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. Eva kerbal\u00A0and let it go of\u00A0cockpit.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLog start just before Eva:.\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://pastebin.com/f2907wMM\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://pastebin.com/f2907wMM\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFull flight log: (i hope)\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://pastebin.com/KLP3bg1W\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://pastebin.com/KLP3bg1W\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPs. Sorry English\u00A0is not my first language.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002284168ABE173D6FF1831C88D35723B02E1BD2895A\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://images.akamai.steamusercontent.com/ugc/97230430500966131/84168ABE173D6FF1831C88D35723B02E1BD2895A/\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002215E0A7056D5899EDD14422CC9C1EA6CD39373AE4\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://images.akamai.steamusercontent.com/ugc/97230430500966608/15E0A7056D5899EDD14422CC9C1EA6CD39373AE4/\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nScreenshots\u00A0made after 15-20 sec after Jeb goes eva\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Found 1 error in text\u0022\u003E\n1\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Found 1 error in text\u0022\u003E\n1\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUPD. Just launched a ship to the Mun. The same effect happens here but significantly slower/weaker. It appears to be based on celestial body gravitation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-03-12T16:33:57Z\u0022 title=\u002203/12/2017 04:33  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 12, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by grixt\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}